# Compass Blade Full Audit And 3D Rebuild - 2026-05-25

## Case Name

`compass_blade_full_audit_and_3d_rebuild_2026-05-25`

## User Request

- Review all code implemented as `compassBlade` / 나침반 칼날.
- Rebuild the in-game 3D graphic using the connected icon image as the approved 2D source art.
- Fix the current in-game manifestation bug.
- Use three or more agents.

## Classification

- Debugging
- Code review
- Gameplay implementation
- Graphics redesign
- QA validation

## Primary Methodology

- Superpowers systematic debugging
- Superpowers test-driven development
- Project policy department ownership

## Supporting Methodology

- Agent Room routing
- Project graphic policy: 2D source art first, then 3D toon implementation
- Runtime/browser validation after implementation

## Selected Agents

- `code-mapper` - read-only
  - Maps every `compassBlade` code and document touchpoint.
- `reviewer` - read-only
  - Reviews correctness, regressions, missing tests, and risky implementation details.
- `game-developer` - read-only analysis first, write-capable only if explicitly reassigned
  - Analyzes gameplay behavior, collision, orbit timing, and damage flow.
- `graphic_designer` - read-only analysis first, graphics authority for `Graphic_designer/`
  - Interprets `10_wea_compass.png.png` as source art and defines the 3D toon rebuild direction.
- `qa-expert` - read-only analysis first, QA record authority for `Quaility_Assurance/`
  - Defines regression and runtime validation gates.

## Required Output Folders

- `Developer/`
  - Code map, implementation notes, and technical debugging record.
- `Graphic_designer/`
  - 2D source-art interpretation and 3D visual direction.
- `Quaility_Assurance/`
  - Test plan, validation result, and residual risk.
- `Planner/`
  - Reference only unless weapon role, balance, unlock condition, or progression rule changes.

## Verification Gate

- Confirm current implementation against Planner weapon rules.
- Add a failing regression test before production code changes.
- Fix the root cause, not only the symptom.
- Verify with targeted tests and production build.
- Confirm runtime icon/asset availability and visual behavior where possible.
- Record QA result before claiming completion.

## Do Not Skip

- Do not bypass `project_develop_policy.md`.
- Do not treat temporary shapes as final graphics.
- Do not implement graphics without referencing `Graphic_designer/Bang_survivor_Graphic_concept.md`.
- Do not change balance or unlock rules without Planner record.
- Do not overwrite unrelated dirty work.

